===Noun===
'''injunction'''

#The act of [[enjoin]]ing; the act of directing, [[command]]ing, or prohibiting.
#That which is enjoined; an order; a mandate; a decree; a command; a precept; a direction.
#{{law}} A [[writ]] or process, granted by a [[court of equity]], and, in some cases, under [[statute]]s, by a court of law, whereby a party is required to do or to refrain from doing certain acts, according to the [[exigency]] of the writ.

